1
00:00:00,800 --> 00:00:03,980
Listen. Do you hear the drum?

2
00:00:04,030 --> 00:00:07,210
It has been beating the same rhythm since nineteen seventy-four...

3
00:00:07,260 --> 00:00:10,440
at every Haiti match. Without missing one.

4
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:13,540
Tonight... it beats for Brazil.

5
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:21,350
In episode six, we predicted the champions would survive Algeria, one-nil.

6
00:00:21,400 --> 00:00:26,250
Tonight — the kings of football... meet the nation that refuses to break.

7
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:31,350
Welcome back to WorldCup twenty-six Legends, episode seven. Brazil versus Haiti.

8
00:00:31,400 --> 00:00:35,750
Group C. Five stars against one unbreakable heart.

9
00:00:37,500 --> 00:00:41,040
And stay with me — because in first-half stoppage time of our story...

10
00:00:41,090 --> 00:00:44,630
a supermarket worker does something impossible.

11
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:50,955
First, the history. Nineteen seventy-four.

12
00:00:51,005 --> 00:00:55,460
Haiti — the first Caribbean nation ever at a World Cup — walks out against mighty Italy.

13
00:00:57,000 --> 00:00:59,883
Italy's goalkeeper is Dino Zoff.

14
00:00:59,933 --> 00:01:02,817
He has not conceded a goal in one thousand one hundred and forty-two minutes.

15
00:01:02,867 --> 00:01:05,750
The longest wall in football history.

16
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:11,910
Forty-sixth minute. Emmanuel Sanon runs onto a pass... rounds Zoff... and scores.

17
00:01:11,960 --> 00:01:15,370
The wall falls.

18
00:01:16,500 --> 00:01:20,120
Haiti lost that match.

19
00:01:20,170 --> 00:01:23,790
But Sanon's goal became a flag — proof, forever, that the small can wound the giant.

20
00:01:29,500 --> 00:01:33,435
Fifty-two years later — through earthquakes, through everything — Haiti is BACK.

21
00:01:33,485 --> 00:01:37,420
And waiting for them... the kings.

22
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:42,310
Five World Cups. The only nation that has played in every single one.

23
00:01:44,500 --> 00:01:48,040
Vinicius Junior — the dancer. Twenty-five. Champions League royalty.

24
00:01:48,090 --> 00:01:51,630
His feet move faster than the music.

25
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:59,955
Neymar — thirty-four, his very last World Cup, playing with the freedom of a man with nothing left to prove.

26
00:02:00,005 --> 00:02:05,360
Raphinha tortures the flanks. And Alisson... the calmest man alive.

27
00:02:06,500 --> 00:02:10,710
For Brazil, anything less than victory... is a national emergency.

28
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:17,505
But Haiti did not cross the sea to bow.

29
00:02:17,555 --> 00:02:21,060
This is the first Caribbean fairy tale in fifty-two years — and it has teeth.

30
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:27,810
Duckens Nazon. A scout found him stacking shelves in a supermarket.

31
00:02:27,860 --> 00:02:32,170
Now he leads a World Cup attack — wearing that story like armor.

32
00:02:33,500 --> 00:02:36,663
Derrick Etienne Junior — born in America, he chose Haiti.

33
00:02:36,713 --> 00:02:39,877
Johny Placide, the wall of Port-au-Prince.

34
00:02:39,927 --> 00:02:43,090
And all of them know Sanon's story by heart.

35
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:47,370
A nation that survives everything... fears nothing.

36
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:54,270
And the duel inside the match: Neymar against Nazon. The man who has everything...

37
00:02:54,320 --> 00:02:59,090
against the man who came from nothing. Both play for pure joy.

38
00:03:00,500 --> 00:03:04,095
Our prediction — built on five stars, on samba... and on one drum that never stops.

39
00:03:04,145 --> 00:03:07,740
Watch.

40
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:12,550
Twenty-three minutes — Vinicius, goal. Thirty-four — a Neymar free kick.

41
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:16,650
Forty-one — Raphinha. Three-nil.

42
00:03:17,900 --> 00:03:20,750
Three-nil before half time. The match is over. Everyone knows it...

43
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:23,650
everyone except one man.

44
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:32,120
Stoppage time. Nazon takes the ball on the halfway line.

45
00:03:32,170 --> 00:03:37,290
Not fast, by Brazilian standards. Not skillful, by Brazilian standards. But Haitian.

46
00:03:38,500 --> 00:03:42,160
Past one. Past two. He shoots from the edge of the box —

47
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:48,685
TOP CORNER! NAZON!

48
00:03:48,735 --> 00:03:52,420
The supermarket worker scores against BRAZIL — and the whole stadium rises!

49
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:56,077
Brazil add a fourth — Neymar, barely a celebration.

50
00:03:56,127 --> 00:03:59,203
Because tonight the scoreline is not the story.

51
00:03:59,253 --> 00:04:02,330
The story is the goal that made the world stand up.

52
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:06,910
Do you agree? Comment SAMBA if Brazil win the Hexa this summer.

53
00:04:06,960 --> 00:04:10,370
Comment SPIRIT if Nazon's goal is the moment of the tournament.

54
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:15,933
And the drum? Legend number eight: Le Tambouye de soixante-quatorze.

55
00:04:15,983 --> 00:04:19,417
They say he beat that drum in the stands in nineteen seventy-four...

56
00:04:19,467 --> 00:04:22,900
and he has never stopped.

57
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:30,240
Tonight, the drum beat for a miracle. Collect him inside the game.

58
00:04:32,500 --> 00:04:35,653
Which brings us to YOU.

59
00:04:35,703 --> 00:04:38,857
At WorldCup twenty-six dot world, pick three of the forty-eight nations — and every goal they score...

60
00:04:38,907 --> 00:04:42,060
scores for you.

61
00:04:43,900 --> 00:04:48,940
Free to play. Live leaderboard. Underdogs pay triple — like Haiti tonight.

62
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:53,820
Hit like — send this to the friend who stopped believing in miracles.

63
00:04:53,870 --> 00:04:57,490
And subscribe: the legends are only beginning.

